-- changing from module based to standalone :true
01
Enable standalone bootstrapIn main.ts, replace bootstrapModule(AppModule) with bootstrapApplication(AppComponent, { providers: [...] }).
02
Convert root componentMark AppComponent with standalone: true and move BrowserModule, RouterModule, HttpClientModule, FormsModule, ReactiveFormsModule into its imports.
03
Refactor feature componentsGradually mark feature components as standalone: true and add CommonModule, RouterModule, or ReactiveFormsModule to their imports as needed.
04
Replace NgModulesRemove NgModules like AppModule or SharedModule. Instead, import standalone components, directives, and pipes directly where they are used.
05
Handle shared utilitiesFor reusable components (e.g., DefaultImageComponent), make them standalone and import them into other components instead of declaring them in a SharedModule.
06
Update routingUse provideRouter(routes) in bootstrapApplication instead of RouterModule.forRoot. Feature routes can import standalone components directly.
07
Clean up providersMove services and interceptors into bootstrapApplication providers or provide them in standalone components using the providers array.

